# CINs Performance Rules

Read `docs/CINS_DEV_RULES.md` §5 and §8 before changing page load, data fetching, image/media, editor upload, route rendering, or heavy UI.

- Supabase list queries must select only needed columns, use pagination (`.range`) from the start, and avoid N+1 by embedding relations or batching.
- Public pages should favor SSR/SSG/streaming with static shell first. Split data-heavy sections into async Server Components under `<Suspense>` with CINS-token skeletons and `loading.tsx` where useful.
- Internal navigation must use `next/link`; avoid raw `<a href>` for app routes.
- Images should use Cloudflare Images IDs/variants, include dimensions when possible, lazy-load below the fold, and use eager/fetch priority only for above-the-fold images.
- Upload UX should be optimistic: show local preview immediately, upload in background/Direct Upload, handle failure/retry, and avoid saving temporary `blob:` URLs.
- Heavy non-critical UI (editor, chart, map, rich widgets) should be route-split or lazy-loaded. Avoid adding dependencies without checking bundle size.
- User input search/filter that hits APIs should be debounced around 300ms.
- For long lists (>100 items), use virtualization or pagination; show skeleton/empty states instead of blank spinners.
- Do not add cache layers (`unstable_cache`, `revalidate`, SWR/TanStack Query) casually; choose them only when task scope calls for it and document invalidation.
- Before committing performance-sensitive public pages, test under slow network and aim for Lighthouse > 85 on the changed page.
